Circle
  Type 2
  Pos 271 408
  Text §Obviously you do not spend any time away from the city to ask such questions. Why, `tis nothing more than the name of the sea. The story goes, that the rains are quite heavy the farther you go away from the shore. It is supposed to have something to do with Mordeas powers. Part of her role as ruling Tempest is to control the rain over the city, but she feels no obligation to extend that to the distant waters. Of course, I never had an unwanted cloud while out to sea myself, so I suspect the name is more rumor than truth. §
End

